### HR Management System API Requests

### Environment Variables
# @name baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api

### Security workflow (JWT access + refresh)
### 0. Register user (you can pass any roles except ROLE_ADMIN)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "candidate1",
  "email": "candidate1@example.com",
  "password": "StrongPass!23",
  "roles": ["ROLE_CANDIDATE", "ROLE_HR", "ROLE_INTERVIEWER"]
}

### 1) Login: get access + refresh token pair
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "candidate1",
  "password": "StrongPass!23"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("accessToken", response.body.accessToken);
  client.global.set("refreshToken", response.body.refreshToken);
%}

### 2) Protected endpoint with access token (must be 200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/vacancies
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 3) Refresh token (get new pair)
# @name refreshOnce
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("newAccessToken", response.body.accessToken);
  client.global.set("newRefreshToken", response.body.refreshToken);
%}

### 4) Reuse old refresh token (must be 401/403)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### 5) (DB check) user_sessions statuses:
### old session -> REFRESHED, new session -> ACTIVE

### 1. Create Vacancy
POST {{baseUrl}}/vacancies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Senior Java Developer",
  "description": "We are looking for an experienced Java developer with Spring Boot experience.",
  "location": "Moscow",
  "salary": 250000,
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "hrManager": "Ivan Petrov"
}

### 2. Get All Vacancies
GET {{baseUrl}}/vacancies

### 3. Get Active Vacancies
GET {{baseUrl}}/vacancies/active

### 4. Create Candidate
POST {{baseUrl}}/candidates
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "email": "john.smith@example.com",
  "phone": "+7 (999) 123-45-67",
  "experience": "5 years of Java development",
  "skills": "Java, Spring Boot, PostgreSQL, Docker",
  "resumeUrl": "https://example.com/resume/john-smith.pdf"
}

### 5. Get All Candidates
GET {{baseUrl}}/candidates

### 6. Apply for Vacancy (Business Operation 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/recruitment/apply
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vacancyId": 1,
  "candidateId": 1,
  "coverLetter": "I am very interested in this position and believe my skills match your requirements."
}

### 7. Get All Applications
GET {{baseUrl}}/applications

### 8. Schedule Interview (Business Operation 2)
POST {{baseUrl}}/recruitment/schedule-interview
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "applicationId": 1,
  "interviewer": "Maria Ivanova",
  "scheduledTime": "2026-02-25T14:00:00",
  "durationMinutes": 60
}

### 9. Get All Interviews
GET {{baseUrl}}/interviews

### 10. Get Upcoming Interviews
GET {{baseUrl}}/interviews/upcoming

### 11. Update Interview Status (Complete Interview)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/interviews/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "applicationId": 1,
  "interviewer": "Maria Ivanova",
  "scheduledTime": "2026-02-25T14:00:00",
  "durationMinutes": 60,
  "status": "COMPLETED",
  "type": "TECHNICAL",
  "notes": "Candidate showed strong technical skills"
}

### 12. Update Application Status (After Interview)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/applications/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vacancyId": 1,
  "candidateId": 1,
  "coverLetter": "I am very interested in this position and believe my skills match your requirements.",
  "status": "INTERVIEW_COMPLETED"
}

### 13. Create Offer (Business Operation 3)
POST {{baseUrl}}/recruitment/create-offer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "applicationId": 1,
  "salary": 260000,
  "startDate": "2026-03-15",
  "terms": "Standard employment contract with 20 days vacation"
}

### 14. Get All Offers
GET {{baseUrl}}/offers

### 15. Get Pending Offers
GET {{baseUrl}}/offers/pending

### 16. Accept Offer (Business Operation 4)
POST {{baseUrl}}/recruitment/accept-offer/1

### 17. Get Vacancy Statistics (Business Operation 5)
GET {{baseUrl}}/recruitment/vacancy/1/statistics

### 18. Search Candidates by Skill
GET {{baseUrl}}/candidates/skill/Java

### 19. Search Vacancies by Keyword
GET {{baseUrl}}/vacancies/search?keyword=Java

### 20. Get Applications by Vacancy
GET {{baseUrl}}/applications/vacancy/1

### 21. Get Applications by Candidate
GET {{baseUrl}}/applications/candidate/1

### 22. Get Offers by Candidate
GET {{baseUrl}}/offers/candidate/1

### 23. Create Another Candidate for Testing
POST {{baseUrl}}/candidates
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Alice",
  "lastName": "Johnson",
  "email": "alice.johnson@example.com",
  "phone": "+7 (999) 987-65-43",
  "experience": "3 years of Java development",
  "skills": "Java, Spring, MySQL, Git",
  "resumeUrl": "https://example.com/resume/alice-johnson.pdf"
}

### 24. Second Candidate Applies for Same Vacancy
POST {{baseUrl}}/recruitment/apply
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vacancyId": 1,
  "candidateId": 2,
  "coverLetter": "I would like to apply for this position as I have relevant experience."
}

### 25. Try to Apply Again (Should Fail - Duplicate Application)
POST {{baseUrl}}/recruitment/apply
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vacancyId": 1,
  "candidateId": 1,
  "coverLetter": "Second attempt to apply"
}

### 26. Create Second Vacancy
POST {{baseUrl}}/vacancies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Middle Java Developer",
  "description": "Looking for a middle-level Java developer.",
  "location": "St. Petersburg",
  "salary": 180000,
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "hrManager": "Elena Sidorova"
}

### 27. Schedule Conflicting Interview (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/recruitment/schedule-interview
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "applicationId": 2,
  "interviewer": "Maria Ivanova",
  "scheduledTime": "2026-02-25T14:30:00",
  "durationMinutes": 60
}

### 28. Create Second Offer for Same Candidate (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/recruitment/create-offer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "applicationId": 2,
  "salary": 200000,
  "startDate": "2026-03-20",
  "terms": "Standard contract"
}
